Manjaro list of things to do for proper setup on PineBook Pro:

Connect to WiFi
Configure touchpad click on tap
Add shortcut pine xfce4-popup-whiskermenu
sudo pacman-mirrors --fasttrack 20 && sudo pacman -Syyu
pamac install vim neovim tmux bat
Deactivate upgrades from Software manager preferences
Add .vimrc from github.com/desaxce/config and set modelines=0
Use .bashrc https://gist.github.com/zachbrowne/8bc414c9f30192067831fafebd14255c
Windows Manager - tile window top/bottom/left right shortcuts (Alt-F11 full screen)
pamac remove matray and remove from Session & startup config
Configure Firefox - search engine, privacy settings - Guide Manjaro bookmark
Pine+E shortcut to run thunar Downloads
pamac install libreoffice transmission-gtk chromium
pamac install tlp (to have "bluetooth toggle", shortcut to configure - pine+b)
Install copyq with alt+v shortcut (inside the copyq preferences)
Add Chromium to panel and Libreoffice Writer
Change locale (locale.gen add french + /etc/locale.conf)
Keyboard settings: add french layout, don't use system default and config alt+shift as switch shortcut (add flag on panel taskbar - to see keyboard layout)

